Licence: New BSD Licence (see the file LICENSE for details)

Prerequisites (optional):
  - ImageMagick (optional)
  - Ghostscript (optional)

Compile and install with:
  configure
  make
  make install

The software will compile and install in turn:
 - Ocaml
 - Camlp5
 - Coq
 - zenon
 - zvtov
 - focalizec

For checking the proofs with coqc, add this to your $HOME/.coqrc file:
  Add LoadPath "/usr/local/lib/zenon".
If you specified an alternate libdir when configuring focalize, you will
need to adjust this command accordingly.

Web site: http://focalize.inria.fr/
Discussion: focalize-users@inria.fr
Bug reports for installation: Pierre.Weis@inria.fr
Bug reports for the compiler: http://focalize.inria.fr/
 (Find and click on the ``Bug Tracking'' link)
Contact developers: focalize-devel@inria.fr
